{
  "video_id": "MVSbwNZca9Q",
  "title": "Felony Sentencing in California (a former DA explains)",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 6800.0,
      "end_time": 10240.0,
      "text": "Today, I want to give a quick overview of felony sentencing"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 10240.0,
      "end_time": 11790.0,
      "text": "in California."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 11790.0,
      "end_time": 14719.0,
      "text": "So if you&#39;re convicted of a felony,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 14720.0,
      "end_time": 17250.0,
      "text": "you will have a sentencing hearing"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 17250.0,
      "end_time": 20430.0,
      "text": "where the judge will decide what sentence"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 20430.0,
      "end_time": 22480.0,
      "text": "or what penalties to impose."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 22480.0,
      "end_time": 25230.0,
      "text": "And at a sentencing hearing, the judge really"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 25230.0,
      "end_time": 27790.0,
      "text": "has two calls to make-- first of all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 27790.0,
      "end_time": 29200.0,
      "text": "whether to grant probation."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 29200.0,
      "end_time": 32490.0,
      "text": "Almost every crime allows the judge discretion"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 32490.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34610.0,
      "text": "to grant probation, and this is where"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 34610.0,
      "end_time": 37250.0,
      "text": "the judge says, basically, \"I&#39;m going to go easy on you."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 37250.0,
      "end_time": 38830.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to give you a chance."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 38830.0,
      "end_time": 40769.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m going to put you on probation.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 40770.0,
      "end_time": 43340.0,
      "text": "Now, with probation, the judge can still"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 43340.0,
      "end_time": 47600.0,
      "text": "sentence you to up to a year in county jail."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 47600.0,
      "end_time": 49570.0,
      "text": "But oftentimes, when the judge grants probation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 49570.0,
      "end_time": 51200.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s no jail time at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 51200.0,
      "end_time": 52960.0,
      "text": "The judge merely says, \"I&#39;m going"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 52960.0,
      "end_time": 56230.0,
      "text": "to have you on probation for three to five years."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 56230.0,
      "end_time": 58970.0,
      "text": "And if you do everything correctly, at the end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 58970.0,
      "end_time": 61430.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ll dismiss your case and expunge it."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 61430.0,
      "end_time": 64230.0,
      "text": "If you violate your probation, then we"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 64230.00000000001,
      "end_time": 68370.0,
      "text": "can send you to jail or prison for up to the maximum term.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 68370.0,
      "end_time": 71770.0,
      "text": "If the judge elects not to grant probation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 71770.0,
      "end_time": 74570.0,
      "text": "then the judge has to decide-- do I impose"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 74570.0,
      "end_time": 77590.0,
      "text": "a low, middle, or high term?"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 77600.0,
      "end_time": 81200.0,
      "text": "Now, almost every crime has a sentencing range"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 81200.0,
      "end_time": 82800.0,
      "text": "of a low middle or high term."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 82800.0,
      "end_time": 86300.0,
      "text": "For example, grand theft has a low term"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 86300.0,
      "end_time": 90170.0,
      "text": "of 16 months in custody, a middle term"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 90170.0,
      "end_time": 93840.0,
      "text": "of two years in custody, and a high term"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 93840.0,
      "end_time": 96100.0,
      "text": "of three years in custody."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 96100.0,
      "end_time": 99180.0,
      "text": "Generally, the middle term is presumed"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 99180.0,
      "end_time": 103400.0,
      "text": "unless there are mitigating or aggravating circumstances."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 103400.0,
      "end_time": 106800.0,
      "text": "Now, mitigating circumstances are things in your case"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 106800.0,
      "end_time": 109330.0,
      "text": "that would call for leniency."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 109330.0,
      "end_time": 112470.0,
      "text": "So for example, if you have no prior record,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 112470.0,
      "end_time": 115780.0,
      "text": "if you played only a small role in the crime,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 115780.0,
      "end_time": 119460.0,
      "text": "if you took care to make sure that nobody got hurt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 119460.0,
      "end_time": 122309.0,
      "text": "if your motive for committing the crime"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 122310.0,
      "end_time": 125660.0,
      "text": "was to provide food for your children-- all of these"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 125660.0,
      "end_time": 128740.0,
      "text": "would be considered mitigating factors."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 128740.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131000.00000000001,
      "text": "Then there&#39;s aggravating factors."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 131000.0,
      "end_time": 133390.0,
      "text": "Aggravating factors are things that would"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 133390.0,
      "end_time": 136109.0,
      "text": "call for a tougher sentence."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 136110.0,
      "end_time": 139170.0,
      "text": "So for example, if you have an extensive record,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 139170.0,
      "end_time": 141679.0,
      "text": "if you were already on probation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 141680.0,
      "end_time": 146180.0,
      "text": "if you used a weapon, if multiple people were injured,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 146180.0,
      "end_time": 150300.0,
      "text": "or there was a great loss of money to the victim,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 150300.0,
      "end_time": 154400.0,
      "text": "these would be considered aggravating circumstances."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 154400.0,
      "end_time": 156760.0,
      "text": "So basically, the judge weighs the mitigating"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 156760.0,
      "end_time": 158980.0,
      "text": "and the aggravating circumstances."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 158980.0,
      "end_time": 163850.0,
      "text": "If the mitigating circumstances outweigh the aggravating"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 163850.0,
      "end_time": 167690.0,
      "text": "circumstances, then the judge is supposed"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 167690.0,
      "end_time": 169560.0,
      "text": "to impose the low term."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 169560.0,
      "end_time": 172800.0,
      "text": "On the other hand, in a more serious case"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 172800.0,
      "end_time": 174630.0,
      "text": "where the aggravating circumstances outweigh"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 174630.0,
      "end_time": 177510.0,
      "text": "the mitigating circumstances, the judge"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 177510.0,
      "end_time": 180310.0,
      "text": "is supposed to impose the high term."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 180310.0,
      "end_time": 184370.0,
      "text": "This is where a good criminal defense attorney comes in."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 184370.0,
      "end_time": 187900.0,
      "text": "We can emphasize the mitigating factors"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 187900.0,
      "end_time": 190900.0,
      "text": "and show why the aggravating factors should be discounted."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 190900.0,
      "end_time": 193720.0,
      "text": "At a sentencing hearing, a good defense attorney"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 193720.0,
      "end_time": 197100.0,
      "text": "can go a long way towards convincing the judge"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 197100.0,
      "end_time": 201359.0,
      "text": "to impose a low term or to grant probation and impose no jail"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 201360.0,
      "end_time": 203300.0,
      "text": "time at all."
    }
  ]
}